table asyncio_extra114.asyncio_boundedsemaphore_identity_methods:
  description: "asyncio.BoundedSemaphore class identity and method qualname checks in asynciocond114 namespace — wave 255 theme: asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__name__.__eq__('BoundedSemaphore')==True (len=16: 'BoundedSemaphore'=16; a Semaphore subclass that raises ValueError if released more times than acquired); asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__name__.__len__()==16; asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__qualname__.__eq__('BoundedSemaphore')==True (len=16; qualname equals name); asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__module__.__eq__('asyncio.locks')==True (len=13; same module as Condition and Semaphore); asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__mro__.__len__()==5 (MRO=[BoundedSemaphore, Semaphore, _ContextManagerMixin, _LoopBoundMixin, object]; deepest MRO in this spec — one deeper than Semaphore=4 because BoundedSemaphore inherits from Semaphore); asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('Semaphore')==True (BoundedSemaphore is a direct subclass of Semaphore — compare: Condition.__bases__[0].__name__=='_ContextManagerMixin' — Condition does not inherit from Semaphore); asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__('BoundedSemaphore.__init__')==True (len=25: 'BoundedSemaphore.'=17+'__init__'=8=25; BoundedSemaphore defines its own __init__ — co_argcount=2: self and value); asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__init__.__qualname__.__len__()==25; asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__init__.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(2)==True; asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.release.__qualname__.__eq__('BoundedSemaphore.release')==True (len=24: 'BoundedSemaphore.'=17+'release'=7=24; BoundedSemaphore overrides Semaphore.release to add the bounds check; co_argcount=1: self only); asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.release.__qualname__.__len__()==24; asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.release.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(1)==True; compare qualname lengths: BoundedSemaphore.release=24 < BoundedSemaphore.__init__=25 (longest in spec); compare: BoundedSemaphore.locked and BoundedSemaphore.acquire are inherited from Semaphore, so their qualnames use 'Semaphore.' prefix (not 'BoundedSemaphore.'); compare class name lengths: Condition=9 < BoundedSemaphore=16 (7 chars longer); verified with Python 3.14.3"
